Reasoning: The paper introduces a new distributed graph database that enables efficient, transactional graph analyses as well as strictly serializable ACID transactions on dynamic graphs. This makes it likely to belong to the categories of databases (cs.DB), distributed systems (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and distributed computing (cs.Distributed). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of refinable timestamps as a novel request ordering mechanism, which could also place it in the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
